{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a0eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a11",
    "name": "Tokenized Assets API",
    "description": "All HTTP routes from `AdminPingController`, `AdminRestController`, `ClientPingController`, and `ClientChainController` (global prefix **`/v1`**).\n\n## Collection variables\nReplace **`exampleAssetMint`**, **`exampleAssetPda`**, **`exampleWallet`**, **`exampleRedemptionId`**, **`exampleTxSignature`**, and **`exampleChallengeId`** with values from your chain / flows. Defaults use the native mint pubkey as a stand-in Solana address.\n\n## Environment\nImport **`local.postman_environment.json`** and set **ADMIN_HMAC_SECRET** and **CLIENT_HMAC_SECRET** (≥32 chars, match backend `.env`).\n\n## HMAC\nThe pre-request script uses **CryptoJS** (SHA-256 + HMAC-SHA256 hex) — not Node `require('crypto')`, which Postman Web and some sandboxes block. Resolution order: global `CryptoJS` → `require('crypto-js')` → `pm.require('crypto-js')`. If signing fails, add the **crypto-js** package in Postman’s Package Library for this workspace.\n\nCanonical: `METHOD\\nPATH\\nTIMESTAMP\\nBODY_SHA256_HEX` (+ `\\nNONCE` for POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE). Path = pathname only (no `?query`). **`/v1/health*`** skips HMAC.\n\nAdmin mutating routes include **`Idempotency-Key: {{$guid}}`** per controller.\n\n## Swagger\n`GET {{baseUrl}}/docs/admin` · `GET {{baseUrl}}/docs/client` when `SWAGGER_ENABLED=true`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
